==Getting started==
===Talking to Redbeard Frank===
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, Matey!
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|I'm in search of treasure.}}
** '''Player:''' I'm in search of treasure.
** '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, treasure you be after eh? Well I might be able to tell you where to find some... For a price...
** '''Player:''' What sort of price?
** '''Redbeard Frank:''' Well for example if you can get me a bottle of rum... Not just any rum mind...
** '''Redbeard Frank:''' I'd like some rum made on Karamja Island. There's no rum like Karamja Rum!
** {{tcond|If the player has completed Rum Deal:}}
*** '''Player:''' Would some Braindeath 'Rum' do?
*** '''Redbeard Frank:''' Gadzooks, that swill! Not a chance!
*** '''Redbeard Frank:''' It's Karamja Rum or no deal.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{tselect|Start the Pirate's Treasure quest?}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' Ok, I will bring you some rum.
*** '''Redbeard Frank:''' Yer a saint, although it'll take a miracle to get it off Karamja.
*** '''Player:''' What do you mean?
*** '''Redbeard Frank:''' The Customs office has been clampin' down on the export of spirits. You seem like a resourceful young [lad/lass], I'm sure ye'll be able to find a way to slip the stuff past them.
*** '''Player:''' Well I'll give it a shot.
*** '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, that's the spirit!
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No.}}
*** '''Player:''' Not right now.
*** '''Redbeard Frank:''' Fair enough. I'll still be here and thirsty whenever you feel like helpin' out.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=no|Arr!}}
* {{topt|quest=no|Do you have anything for trade?}}

===Talking to Redbeard Frank again===
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, Matey!
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Have ye brought some rum for yer ol' mate Frank?
* '''Player:''' No, not yet.
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Not surprising, tis no easy task to get it off Karamja.
* '''Player:''' What do you mean?
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' The Customs office has been clampin' down on the export of spirits. You seem like a resourceful young lad, I'm sure ye'll be able to find a way to slip the stuff past them.
* '''Player:''' Well I'll give it another shot.
* {{tact|end}}

==Visiting Karamja==
===Talking to Luthas===
* '''Luthas:''' Hello I'm Luthas, I run the banana plantation here.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Could you offer me employment on your plantation?}}
** '''Player:''' Could you offer me employment on your plantation?
** '''Luthas:''' Yes, I can sort something out. There's a crate ready to be loaded onto the ship.
** '''Luthas:''' You wouldn't believe the demand for bananas from Wydin's shop over in Port Sarim. I think this is the third crate I've shipped him this month..
** '''Luthas:''' If you could fill it up with bananas, I'll pay you 30 gold.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|That customs officer is annoying isn't she?}}
** '''Player:''' That customs officer is annoying isn't she?
** '''Luthas:''' Well I know her pretty well. She doesn't cause me any trouble any more.
** '''Luthas:''' She doesn't even search my export crates any more. She knows they only contain bananas.
** '''Player:''' Really? How interesting. Whereabouts do you send those to?
** '''Luthas:''' There is a little shop over in Port Sarim that buys them up by the crate. I believe it is run by a man called Wydin.
** {{tact|end}}

===Filling the crate with bananas===
* {{tcond|If the player uses an individual banana on the crate:}}
** {{tbox|You pack a banana into the crate.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player selects the Fill option on the crate:}}
** {{tbox|You pack all your bananas into the crate.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player attempts to add an 11th banana in the crate:}}
** {{mes|The crate is already full.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Using Karamjan rum on Crate===
* {{tcond|If the crate does not have a Karamjan rum already stored:}}
** {{tbox|You stash the rum in the crate.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player attempts to store another Karamjan rum in the crate:}}
** {{mes|There's already some rum in here...}}
** {{tact|end}}

====Attempting to hide Karamjan rum (banana) in the crate====
* {{tbox|Pirates don't usually take banana with their Karamjan rum.}}
* {{tact|end}}

====Attempting to hide Karamjan rum (sliced banana) in the crate====
* {{tbox|Pirates don't usually take sliced banana with their Karamjan rum.}}
* {{tact|end}}

====Searching the crate====
* {{tcond|If there are fewer than 10 bananas inside the crate:}}
** {{mes|The crate has # banana[s] inside.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the crate has 10 bananas:}}
** {{tbox|The crate is full of bananas.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has hidden a rum bottle in the crate:}}
** {{tbox|There is also some rum stashed in here too.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Luthas after filling up the crate===
* '''Player:''' I've filled a crate with bananas.
* '''Luthas:''' Well done, here's your payment.
* {{mes|Luthas hands you 30 coins.}}
* {{tact|receives=30 coins}}
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Will you pay me for another crate full?}}
** '''Player:''' Will you pay me for another crate full?
** '''Luthas:''' Yes certainly.
** '''Luthas:''' If you go outside you should see the old crate has been loaded on to the ship, and there is another empty crate in its place.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Thank you, I'll be on my way}}
** '''Player:''' Thank you, I'll be on my way.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|So where are these bananas going to be delivered to?}}
** '''Player:''' So where are these bananas going to be delivered to?
** '''Luthas:''' I sell them to Wydin who runs a grocery store in Port Sarim.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|That customs officer is annoying isn't she?}}
** {{tact|above}}

===Talking to the Customs officer===
* '''Customs officer:''' Can I help you?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Can I journey on this ship?}}
** '''Player:''' Can I journey on this ship?
** '''Customs officer:''' You need to be searched before you can board.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Why?}}
*** '''Player:''' Why?
*** '''Customs officer:''' Because Asgarnia has banned the import of intoxicating spirits.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Search away, I have nothing to hide.}}
*** '''Player:''' Search away, I have nothing to hide.
*** {{tcond|If the player has Karamjan rum:}}
**** '''Customs officer:''' Aha, trying to smuggle rum are we?
**** '''Player:''' Umm... it's for personal use?
**** {{mes|The customs officer confiscates your rum.}}
**** {{mes|You will need to find some way to smuggle it off the island...}}
**** {{tact|end}}
**** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the Ring of Charos(a):}}
***** {{tselect|Select an option}}
***** {{topt|Umm... it's for personal use?}}
****** {{tact|above}}
***** {{topt|(Charm) This is not the Karamja rum you are looking for.}}
****** '''Player:''' This is not the Karamja rum you are looking for.
****** '''Customs officer:''' This is not the Karamja rum we are looking for.
****** '''Player:''' Well that was easy!
****** {{qact|The player performs the dance emote.}}
****** {{mes|You dance for joy...}}
****** {{mes|...and accidentally drop the rum.}}
****** '''Player:''' Drat...
****** {{mes|You will need to try again.}}
*** {{tcond|If the player does not have Karamjan rum:}}
**** '''Customs officer:''' Well you've got some odd stuff, but it's all legal. Now you need to pay a boarding charge of 30 coins.
**** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
**** {{topt|Ok.}}
***** '''Player:''' Ok.
***** {{tcond|If the player doesn't have 30 coins:}}
****** '''Player:''' Oh dear, I don't seem to have enough money.
***** {{tact|end}}
**** {{topt|Oh, I'll not bother then.}}
***** '''Player:''' Oh, I'll not bother then.
***** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|You're not putting your hands on my things!}}
*** '''Player:''' You're not putting your hands on my things!
*** '''Customs officer:''' You're not getting on this ship then.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the Ring of Charos(a):}}
*** {{topt|(Charm) You don't need to look through my things.}}
**** '''Player:''' You don't need to look through my things.
**** '''Customs officer:''' Oh, I think I do. If you don't want to let me search your possessions, then you're not coming aboard this ship.
**** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Does Karamja have unusual customs then?}}
** '''Player:''' Does Karamja have any unusual customs then?
** '''Customs officer:''' I'm not that sort of customs officer.
** {{tact|end}}

==Attempting to smuggle out the rum==
* {{tcond|If the player teleports out using any spell or teleport item:}}
** {{tact|The player is teleported to their target location.}}
** {{mes|Your Karamjan rum gets broken and spilled.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player uses Karamjan rum on an [[imp-in-a-box]]:}}
** '''Imp:''' Don't you know? You can get into trouble for giving alcohol to minors, and I'm pretty small, it has to be said.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player tries to board a player owned boat}}
** {{tbox|The nearby customs agent stops you from using the dock facilities with Karamjan rum in your backpack.}}
** {{tact|end}}

==Retrieving the Rum==
===Talking to Wydin===
* '''Wydin:''' Welcome to my food store! Would you like to buy anything?
* {{topt|quest=no|Yes please.}}
* {{topt|quest=no|No, thank you.}}
* {{topt|quest=no|What can you recommend?}}
* {{topt|Can I get a job here?}}
** '''Player:''' Can I get a job here?
** '''Wydin:''' Well, you're keen, I'll give you that. Okay, I'll give you a go. Have you got your own white apron?
** {{tcond|If the player has a white apron:}}
*** '''Player:''' Yes, I have one right here.
*** '''Wydin:''' Wow - you are well prepared! You're hired. Go through to the back and tidy up for me, please.
*** {{tcond|If the white apron is not equipped:}}
**** '''Wydin:''' You need to put your white apron on first though.
**** {{tact|continues}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player does not have a white apron:}}
*** '''Player:''' No, I haven't.
*** '''Wydin:''' Well, you can't work here unless you have a white apron. Health and safety regulations, you understand.
*** '''Player:''' Where can I get one of those?
*** '''Wydin:''' Well, I get all of mine over at the clothing shop in Varrock. They sell them cheap there.
*** '''Wydin:''' Oh, and I'm sure that I've seen a spare one over in Gerrant's fish store somewhere. It's the little place just north of here.
*** {{tact|end}}

===Trying to open the door in the Food Store before getting the job===
* '''Wydin:''' Hey, you can't go in there. Only employees of the grocery store can go in.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Well, can I get a job here?}}
** {{tact|Same as above from "Can I get a job here?"}}
* {{topt|Sorry, I didn't realise.}}
** '''Player:''' Sorry, I didn't realise.
** {{tact|end}}

===Trying to open the door after getting the job while not wearing a white apron===
* '''Wydin:''' Can you put your white apron on before going in there, please?
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Wydin after getting the job===
* '''Wydin:''' Is it nice and tidy round the back now?
* {{topt|Yes, can I work out front now?}}
** '''Player:''' Yes, can I work out front now?
** '''Wydin:''' No, I'm the one who works here.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Yes, are you going to pay me yet?}}
** '''Player:''' Yes, are you going to pay me yet?
** '''Wydin:''' Umm... No, not yet.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No, it's a complete mess}}
** '''Player:''' No, it's a complete mess.
** '''Wydin:''' Ah well, it'll give you something to do, won't it.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Can I buy something please?}}
** '''Player:''' Can I buy something please?
** '''Wydin:''' Yes, of course.
** {{tact|opens=Food Store}}

===Taking the apron in Gerrant's Fishy Business===
* {{mes|You take an apron. It feels freshly starched and smells of laundry.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Search crate in the Food Store===
* {{mes|There are a lot of bananas in the crate.}}
* {{mes|You find your bottle of rum in amongst the bananas.}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Delivering the rum==
===Offering Frank stuffed banana rum===
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, Matey!
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Have ye brought some rum for yer ol' mate Frank?
* '''Player:''' Yes, I've got some.
* {{tact|(Frank takes the bottle from your inventory, but returns it shortly.)}}
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr - this here rum's got a banana stuck in it!
* {{tact|end}}

===Offering Frank sliced banana rum===
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, Matey!
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Have ye brought some rum for yer ol' mate Frank?
* '''Player:''' Yes, I've got some.
* {{tact|(Frank takes the bottle from your inventory, but returns it shortly.)}}
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr - I don't likes banana in me rum!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Redbeard Frank===
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, Matey!
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Have ye brought some rum for yer ol' mate Frank?
* {{tcond|If the player does not have the rum:}}
** '''Player:''' No, not yet.
** '''Redbeard Frank:''' Not surprising, tis no easy task to get it off Karamja.
** '''Player:''' What do you mean?
** '''Redbeard Frank:''' The Customs office has been clampin' down on the export of spirits. You seem like a resourceful young [lad/lass], I'm sure ye'll be able to find a way to slip the stuff past them.
** '''Player:''' Well I'll give it another shot.
** {{tact|end}}
* '''Player:''' Yes, I've got some.
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Now a deal's a deal, I'll tell ye about the treasure. I used to serve under a pirate captain called One-Eyed Hector.
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Hector were very successful and became very rich. But about a year ago we were boarded by the Customs and Excise Agents.
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Hector were killed along with many of the crew, I were one of the few to escape and I escaped with this.
* {{tbox|pic=Chest key (Pirate's Treasure) detail.png|Frank happily takes the rum... and hands you a key.}}
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' This be Hector's key. I believe it opens his chest in his old room in the Blue Moon Inn in Varrock.
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' With any luck his treasure will be in there.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Ok thanks, I'll go and get it.}}
** '''Player:''' Ok thanks, I'll go and get it.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|So why didn't you ever get it?}}
** '''Player:''' So why didn't you ever get it?
** '''Redbeard Frank:''' I'm not allowed in the Blue Moon Inn. Apparently I'm a drunken trouble maker.
** {{tact|end}}

===Using the rum on Redbeard Frank===
* '''Player:''' Frank, I have some Karamja Rum.
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Now a deal's a deal, I'll tell ye about the treasure. I used to serve under a pirate captain called One-Eyed Hector.
* {{tact|above}}

===Reclaiming the key===
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, Matey!
* '''Player:''' I seem to have lost my chest key...
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' Arr, silly you. Fortunately I took the precaution to have another one made.
* {{tbox|pic=Chest key (Pirate's Treasure) detail.png|Frank hands you a chest key.}}
* {{tact|receives=Chest key}}
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=no|Arr!}}
* {{topt|quest=no|Do you have anything for trade?}}

==Finishing up==
===Opening the Chest===
* {{mes|The chest is locked.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using the key on the Chest===
* {{mes|You unlock the chest.}}
* {{mes|All that's in the chest is a message...}}
* {{mes|You take the message from the chest.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Digging in Falador Park===
* '''Gardener:''' {{overhead|First moles, now this! Take this, vandal!}}

===Digging in Falador Park while being attacked by the Gardener===
* {{mes|I can't dig up anything with him attacking me!}}

===Digging in Falador Park a second time===
* {{mes|You dig a hole in the ground...}}
* {{mes|and find a little chest of treasure.}}
* {{qact|Congratulations! Quest complete!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using the chest on Redbeard Frank after the quest===
* '''Player:''' I have the treasure, would you like a share?
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' No [lad/lass], you got it fair and square.
* '''Redbeard Frank:''' You enjoy it. It's what Hector would have wanted.
* {{tact|end}}

===Opening the casket===
* {{tbox|You open the casket, and find One-Eyed Hector's treasure.}}
* {{tact|end}}
